history.text: Hello, How are you today?
Fab! Hey, what did you think of Iron Man??
I thought it was, and still is the best super hero movie out right now.
How about yourself?
Oh, I totally agree! Even Rotten Tomatoes liked it, and boy oh boy, is that rare! :)
I think rotten tomatoes score is sort of low.
I am surprised it didn't get 8-9 scores.
Oh, yes, I agree there. I was thinking the 94%. I was surprised at the 7.7, myself.
Who was your favorite character?
Jeff Bridges, but I just like him, so I'm biased! Yours?
Really!? My favorite was Downey JR of course. I loved his performance in the film.
What about Bridges was so great for you?
Oh, yes, he was totally great. I love Jeff Bridges from Last Picture Show, so I'm partial to him from his history more than from this.
I can understand that. How did you feel about the story of the movie?
I thought the idea of implanting the magnet to protect him from the shrapnel was awesome!
I was a little disappointed by the business partner betrayal. I think if the movies was just Stark getting revenge on the terrorists would of been better off.

I see what you mean, but I'd say it's more true to life when there's business partner betrayal.......I also love it when people in military companies, etc., are wounded by their own products, like he was.
I think Bridges did fine as a villain, I just think realistically Stark would focus on the war effort rather than an in house struggle with his business partner.
Boy, let me tell you, when you have sneaky dealings at home, it's hard to focus outside! But I see what you mean. I wonder why they called it the Jericho missile?
Yes, I liked how stark's character was brought down to earth and humbled by getting kidnapped by the enemy in the beginning.
I believe Jericho has some kind of religious or all powerful meaning.
It does, indeed, but I wasn't sure exactly what, except it had to do with music!
Oh there is a ton of things it has to do with, songs, movies, games, etc.
That arms trafficking is bad news, but boy, is it prevalent! Even the poet Rimbaud trafficked guns!
Oh, I mean how trumpets were supposed to have toppled the walls of Jericho.
Do you think Stark really knew his weapons were being shared with the enemy?
part of me thinks so.
Really?? I kind of figured he was total good guy.
I love how anyone who wears the suit has the power!
As the movie went on I felt he turned into a good guy.
In the beginning I felt he was just more of a nuetral party.
It's rare when a super hero reveals his identity.
I liked the idea anyone, could wear the suit but im surprised stark didn't have some kind of anti theft measures in it.
I totally agree. I love that concept, as well. I'll assume after the movie, he started working on that anti-theft concept immediately!!!!
I agree, I think stark just didn't care if people knew who he was.
That's what he says now, but wait until the phone starts ringing! LOL!
it more realistic too
Thanks for chatting with me about the film. It was a lot of fun.
It was! Have a great day!
See ya

uid2response.feedback: The other person clearly saw the film, but I tried to hold up my end (I hadn't seen it) and stick to the document as much as possible.
